
@startuml
left to right direction
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor User
actor "Notification System" as NS

rectangle "MicroMeet System" {

  (View Meetups) as UC1
  (View Meetup Details) as UC2
  (Create Meetup) as UC3
  (Join Meetup) as UC4
  (Receive Notifications) as UC5

  User --> UC1
  User --> UC2
  User --> UC3
  User --> UC4

  NS --> UC5

  UC3 .> UC5 : <<include>>
}

note right of User
The User is the primary actor who interacts with MicroMeet to discover
micro meetups, view details, create meetups, and join activities based on
shared interests and real-time availability.
end note

note right of NS
The Notification System is a secondary actor that delivers alerts to users
when meetups are created or updated, when participation changes, or when
important meetup events occur.
end note

note right of UC1
View Meetups allows the user to browse a list of active and upcoming
micro meetups available in the system.
end note

note right of UC2
View Meetup Details allows the user to open a specific meetup and see its
activity, time, location, host, and current participant information.
end note

note right of UC3
Create Meetup allows the user to create a new micro meetup by providing
activity type, time, location, and capacity, which may trigger notifications.
end note

note right of UC4
Join Meetup allows the user to join or request to join a meetup, updating
their participation status for that meetup.
end note

note right of UC5
Receive Notifications represents the system behavior of sending updates to
users when meetups change or when participation-related events occur.
end note

@enduml
